  <body>
    <section name="UnnecessaryPermitsClause">
      <p>Since Checkstyle 13.1.0</p>
      <subsection name="Description" id="UnnecessaryPermitsClause_Description">
        <div>
          Checks for unnecessary permits clauses in sealed classes and interfaces.
        </div>

        <p>
          In the Java programming language, a sealed type may specify a <code>permits</code>
          clause to explicitly list all allowed subclasses. The <code>permits</code> clause is
          optional if all permitted types are nested or declared within the same file.
        </p>

        <p>
          This check tracks:
        <ul>
        <li>the permitted types listed in the <code>permits</code> clause of a sealed type</li>
        <li>all subclasses/implementations found in the same file</li>
        </ul>
          If all permitted types are found in the same compilation unit, a violation is logged.
        </p>
      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Examples" id="UnnecessaryPermitsClause_Examples">
        <p id="Example1-config">
          To configure the check:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="UnnecessaryPermitsClause"/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example1-code">
          To configure the check:
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
public sealed class Example1 permits A, B {
// violation above 'permits clause unnecessary for 'Example1', all subclasses in same file.'
}

final class A extends Example1 {
}

final class B extends Example1 {
}
</code></pre></div><hr class="example-separator"/>
        <p id="Example2-config">
          To configure the check
        </p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="UnnecessaryPermitsClause"/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example2-code">Example:</p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
public sealed interface Example2 permits A, B {
    // ok as all permitted subclasses are not in same file
}

final class A implements Example2 {
}
</code></pre></div>
      </subsection>

